{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d9d2510e-8162-4ff2-b2e9-0e46518f5dd7","content":"\n\nHere's the migration path:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** these packages:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mstestplatform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n   > Note: This requires upgrading to **xUnit v3** (`xunit.v3` instead of `xunit 2.x`). MTP is not supported with xUnit v2.\n\n3. **Add** to your `<PropertyGroup>`:\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n4. **Update** your test code for any xUnit v3 breaking changes (most tests work as-is; notable changes include `Assert.Equal` on collections and some attribute renames).\n\n5. Run tests with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key point:** xUnit v2 doesn't support MTP. You must migrate to **xUnit v3** (currently `xunit.v3` on NuGet). If upgrading to v3 isn't feasible yet, you'll need to stay on VSTest with `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n\nWould you like help with the actual migration of your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"060decba-630d-4192-b374-a5dc602e3fcc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":400},"id":"2eed8683-09d5-49ab-923c-84e22bdbc38b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:36.586Z","parentId":"88093480-a42f-4342-abb2-d42dd1772b0c"}
